ZH: 他真是个可怜的孩子，总是被欺负。
EN: He is such a pitiful child, always being bullied.

ZH: 她看起来很可怜，你应该帮助她。
EN: She looks very pitiful, you should help her.

ZH: 可怜的小猫一直在雨中徘徊。
EN: The pitiful little cat has been wandering in the rain.

ZH: 那个可怜的老人靠捡垃圾为生。
EN: That poor old man makes a living by collecting garbage.

ZH: 可怜的小鸟受伤了，我把它送到了动物医院。
EN: The poor little bird is injured, I took it to the animal hospital.

ZH: 看着她沮丧的样子，我觉得很可怜。
EN: Looking at her dejected look, I feel very pitiful.

ZH: 这个孩子可怜地望着外面的食物。
EN: The child looked pitifully at the food outside.

ZH: 可怜的流浪狗一直追随着我。
EN: The poor stray dog keeps following me.

ZH: 她的家境很可怜，但她不会放弃努力。
EN: Her family is very poor, but she won't give up trying.

ZH: 这个可怜的小女孩每天都要乞讨。
EN: This poor little girl begs every day.

ZH: 看到那些可怜的孩子，我决定成立一个慈善机构。
EN: Seeing those pitiful children, I decided to start a charity organization.

ZH: 他在街上看到一个可怜的乞丐，决定给他一些钱。
EN: He saw a poor beggar on the street and decided to give him some money.

ZH: 雨天，这些可怜的无家可归者只能躲在桥下。
EN: On rainy days, these poor homeless people can only hide under bridges.

ZH: 他想要帮助那些可怜的灾民。
EN: He wants to help those pitiful disaster victims.

ZH: 我们应该尽量帮助那些可怜的家庭。
EN: We should try to help those poor families.

ZH: 老师对这个可怜的学生充满了同情。
EN: The teacher has great sympathy for this poor student.

ZH: 我看到一个可怜的老人在路边求助。
EN: I saw a poor old man asking for help on the roadside.

ZH: 虽然他是个可怜的受害者，但他依然坚强。
EN: Although he is a pitiful victim, he is still strong.

ZH: 那些可怜的灾民等待着救援团队的到来。
EN: The poor disaster victims are waiting for the arrival of the rescue team.

ZH: 这个可怜的孩子常常饿着肚子上学。
EN: This poor child often goes to school on an empty stomach.
